  "number": 2209,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2209",
  "title": "A new API for URL rendering",
  "body": "One of the reccuring problem with the URL sync is that the URL generated are ugly. This is because it is a solution that is meant to work in every case. It's great for prototyping but when you have a better idea of the kind of parameters you will have in your state then it's really a pain.\r\n\r\n### Proposed API\r\n\r\nProvide two functions:\r\n - one that let the user transform the state into a string\r\n - one that does the opposite (harder to code but doable if we prevent an instanciated state)",
